      <div class="row featurette">
        <div class="col-md-7">
          <h2 class="featurette-heading lh-1">Humble Beginnings</h2>
          <p class="lead">
            Wenberg Transfer was founded in 1924 by Sigurd Wenberg in International Falls, Minnesota. Sigurd originally moved to the area in 1910 and worked with his brother, Ben, at his grocery store.  In 1924, he went out on his own, beginning his business by hauling firewood with horses. Sig had married Sarah in 1914, and she provided bookkeeping services for the company while being an active member of the Zion Lutheran Church and raising the couple’s five children. By the late 1920s, Sigurd had transitioned to early trucks, expanding his operations to haul local household goods and eventually delivering mail from the train station, a service the company provided until the late 1960s. The 1930s saw further expansion, with Wenberg Transfer beginning to ship goods out of town. In the 1940s, the company gained the authority to operate across six states, which allowed it to offer household moving services alongside its freight operations. 
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-5">
          <div id="carousel1" class="carousel slide" data-bs-ride="carousel">
            <div class="carousel-inner featurette-carousel">
              <% carousel1Images.forEach((image, index) => { %>
                <div class="carousel-item <%= index === 0 ? 'active' : '' %>">
                  <img src="/assets/feature/featureCarousel1/<%= image %>" class="d-block w-100" alt="Feature image">
                </div>
              <% }) %>
            </div>
            <button class="carousel-control-prev" type="button" data-bs-target="#carousel1" data-bs-slide="prev">
