      <hr class="featurette-divider" />

      <div class="row featurette">
        <div class="col-md-7 order-md-2">
          <h2 class="featurette-heading lh-1">Mid-Century Growth</h2>
          <p class="lead">In 1938, Sigurd’s son, John "John John" Wenberg, joined the company, spending his winters hauling pulpwood and summers moving household goods. When John John left to serve in World War II, Sigurd continued operations with the help of other workers. After John John returned in 1945, the company focused on hauling pulpwood, household goods, and freight, eventually phasing out pulpwood hauling in the 1950s. Wenberg Transfer continued to handle moving and freight services through 1978.
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-5 order-md-1">
          <div id="carousel2" class="carousel slide" data-bs-ride="carousel">
            <div class="carousel-inner featurette-carousel">
